---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteNav from "../components/SiteNav.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
import { SITE } from "../data/site";
---
<Layout title="Hal Proof - Source, License, and Trust Signals" description="Real trust signals for Hal: source repository, MIT license, docs, ReScience Lab context, and transparent product status." path="/testimonials">
  <SiteNav />
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Proof</p>
      <h1>Hal proof and trust signals</h1>
      <p>Before you hand code to an agent loop, you should know what you can inspect. Start with the source, docs, license, and product context—not placeholder logos or invented metrics.</p>
      <div class="btn-row">
        <a class="btn-primary" href={SITE.repoUrl} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">View source on GitHub</a>
        <a class="btn-ghost" href={SITE.rescienceUrl} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Hal on ReScience</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="page-container">
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="info-card"><p class="kicker">Source</p><h3>Public GitHub repository</h3><p>Review the code, README, releases, issues, and license directly instead of trusting a marketing badge.</p></article>
        <article class="info-card"><p class="kicker">License</p><h3>MIT license stated in the site footer</h3><p>The site surfaces the license claim plainly and routes developers to the source repository for confirmation.</p></article>
        <article class="info-card"><p class="kicker">Docs</p><h3>Command-forward docs</h3><p>The getting-started docs show the actual loop commands: init, plan, convert, validate, and run.</p></article>
        <article class="info-card"><p class="kicker">Ecosystem</p><h3>ReScience Lab context</h3><p>Hal is part of the ReScience Lab one-person-company toolchain for agent workflows, pages, research, knowledge, and publishing.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="page-container prose">
      <h2>Why this replaced the trust-logo bar</h2>
      <p>The previous homepage used placeholder brand names as a trust bar. It looked like social proof but gave developers nothing to verify. This version uses inspectable links and avoids customer, adoption, star-count, or testimonial claims that are not sourced in the repo.</p>
      <h2>Want to add real testimonials later?</h2>
      <p>Add named quotes only when the person, company, permission, and exact wording are available. Until then, earn developer trust with source, docs, license, and transparent product behavior.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <SiteFooter />
</Layout>
